snippet.title: The Sims 4 Lovestruck: Official Gameplay Trailer
snippet.description:
Get on the Cupid’s Corner dating app, plan dates with fun Sims, and discover what makes Sims swoon in The Sims™ 4 Lovestruck Expansion Pack*, launching July 25 at 10AM PT. Pre-order or buy through September 5 to get the Heartbreak Happens Digital Content**. 

Finding dates for your Sims has never been easier. Open the new dating app and create a profile – you’ll take a selfie to use as a profile pic and choose which of your Sim’s traits you want to highlight. Then, browse through your matches! These can include both Sims in the world and Sims from the Gallery.

Once you’ve matched with a Sim you’d like to spend time with, start planning your date! Choose the location and which activities you’d like to try together. There are a ton of options including classics like dancing and flirting as well as adventurous options like fishing, swimming, or stargazing. You can even invite additional Sims on your date. Friends, potential partners, or even exes (if you like the drama) can all be invited if you want them to be. 

Whether your date is hot or not could come down to Sims Turn-Ons and Turn-Offs. Some of these are physical, like outfit styles or colors, but others come down to interactions and personality. Those you’ll have to discover. Finding a date is easier than ever, but making relationships work? That’s more of a challenge.

If a date is going poorly, Sims may autonomously decide to leave. 

When Sims become romantically involved, you’ll be able to see how happy they are in their relationships by checking their Romance Satisfaction. Sims can have different levels of satisfaction; what works for one Sim might not work for their partner!

Finding a partner isn't the end of your love story! Relationships will have dynamics, which can be established through gameplay or set in CAS. Will your Sims maintain Wholesome, loving, relationships or happy Steamy relationships? If partners aren't kind things could get Strained. Sims can even have Unpredictable relationships where they switch gears on a dime! 

Explore the fun, flirty side of dating and experience deeper romances in Lovestruck!

Available July 25 at 10 a.m. PT on Origin PC/Mac, Steam, Xbox One, Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation®4, and PlayStation®5. Pre-order now: https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-lovestruck-expansion-pack

*Requires The Sims 4 & all game updates. For PC, see minimum system requirements for the pack.

**Conditions and restrictions apply. See https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/store/addons/the-sims-4-lovestruck-expansion-pack for details.

snippet.title: Sims 2 vs Sims 3 vs Sims 4 - Family Gameplay
snippet.description:
Sims 2 vs Sims 3 vs Sims 4 - Family Gameplay & Dynamics

In this video we take a look at the Family Gameplay of the different Sims games. It touches on Family Relationships, Family Interactions & Gameplay and it slightly covers the Family Dynamics introduced in The Sims 4.

↓Timestamps↓
0:06 Sims 2
8:58 Sims 3
17:04 Sims 4

• Which game do you think has the best Family Gameplay? Put your thoughts down below in the comments section!
_________________________________________________________________________
► Subscribe & like for more videos! 👍
► Complete ''Details In The Sims'' playlist : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LuNDIzFafgk&list=PL0Z9GSKvSnbx-E-0V8ZOqikAYib5n0sAK&index=8
► Complete ''Sims Logic'' playlist : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yro0MzvvHU8&list=PL0Z9GSKvSnbw8BLcUExod51jtBDW7WX0P&ab_channel=Sitycims
_________________________________________________________________________
⇛⇛⇛ Additional Notes ⇚⇚⇚
• TS2 & TS3 : Family drama naturally occurred without my input through the gameplay. 
The only thing I orchestrated were ; Ferdinand's remarriage (TS3) &
the fighting scene (TS3)
• TS4 : No family drama occurred during my gameplay
• TS3 : Children who haven't spoken to a parent for a while might get the
''wants daddy/mommy's attention'' want
• TS4 : Family member can call to gossip about family. Also I remember children sometimes running to hug their parents after work & sims often thinking about their relatives (around 2017 when Parenthood first came out) but I couldn't witness any of that in my recent gameplay.
• There's also baby shower parties (Growing Together)
_________________________________________________________________________
⇛⇛⇛ Additional Resources ⇚⇚⇚
https://sims.fandom.com/wiki/Family_relationships
https://sims.fandom.com/wiki/The_Sims_3:_Generations
_________________________________________________________________________
► Music : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JscGSVJFNXM

snippet.title: OMG Very Brutal & Fatal Truck Accidents
snippet.description:
Certainly! Here are some important safety instructions for driving:

1. *Buckle Up:* Always wear your seatbelt and ensure that all passengers do the same.

2. *Stay Alert:* Avoid distractions like texting, and stay focused on the road.

3. *Obey Speed Limits:* Adhere to posted speed limits and adjust your speed for road conditions.

4. *Maintain a Safe Following Distance:* Keep a safe distance behind the vehicle in front of you to allow for sudden stops.

5. *Use Turn Signals:* Signal your intentions when changing lanes or making turns.

6. *Observe Traffic Signs and Signals:* Follow traffic signals and obey road signs.

7. *Don't Drink and Drive:* Never drive under the influence of alcohol or drugs.

8. *Check Your Blind Spots:* Use your mirrors and turn your head to check blind spots when changing lanes.

9. *Stay within Your Lane:* Maintain your lane discipline and avoid weaving in and out of traffic.

10. *Be Mindful of Weather Conditions:* Adjust your driving to suit the weather, whether it's rain, snow, or fog.

11. *Give Way to Pedestrians:* Yield the right of way to pedestrians at crosswalks and intersections.

12. *Use Your Horn Sparingly:* Honk your horn only to alert other drivers of your presence, not as a form of frustration.

13. *Avoid Aggressive Driving:* Stay calm and patient, and avoid road rage.

14. *Regular Vehicle Maintenance:* Ensure your vehicle is well-maintained with working brakes, lights, and tires.

15. *Stay Informed About Road Conditions:* Be aware of road closures, accidents, or construction on your route.

16. *Use Hands-Free Devices:* If you need to use your phone, use a hands-free device to minimize distractions.

17. *Be Courteous:* Show respect and courtesy to other drivers on the road.

18. *Plan Your Route:* Know your route in advance and have a backup plan in case of unexpected detours.

Remember, safe driving not only protects you but also the people around you. Always prioritize safety on the road.

5. *Use Turn Signals:* Signal your intentions when changing lanes or making turns.

6. *Observe Traffic Signs and Signals:* Follow traffic signals and obey road signs.

7. *Don't Drink and Drive:* Never drive under the influence of alcohol or drugs.

8. *Check Your Blind Spots:* Use your mirrors and turn your head to check blind spots when changing lanes.

9. *Stay within Your Lane:* Maintain your lane discipline and avoid weaving in and out of traffic.

10. *Be Mindful of Weather Conditions:* Adjust your driving to suit the weather, whether it's rain, snow, or fog.

11. *Give Way to Pedestrians:* Yield the right of way to pedestrians at crosswalks and intersections.

12. *Use Your Horn Sparingly:* Honk your horn only to alert other drivers of your presence, not as a form of frustration.

13. *Avoid Aggressive Driving:* Stay calm and patient, and avoid road rage.

14. *Regular Vehicle Maintenance:* Ensure your vehicle is well-maintained with working brakes, lights, and tires.

15. *Stay Informed About Road Conditions:* Be aware of road closures, accidents, or construction on your route.

16. *Use Hands-Free Devices:* If you need to use your phone, use a hands-free device to minimize distractions.

17. *Be Courteous:* Show respect and courtesy to other drivers on the road.

18. *Plan Your Route:* Know your route in advance and have a backup plan in case of unexpected detours.

Remember, safe driving not only protects you but also the people around you. Always prioritize safety on the road.

snippet.title: 4 Year Garden Evolution | How to Start a Garden from Scratch on a Budget
snippet.description:
Go to https://drinkag1.com/myselfreliance to get a FREE 1-year supply of Vitamin D3+K2 and 5 AG1 travel packs with your first purchase. Thanks
 to AG1 for sponsoring today's video!
At the beginning of 2020, I started a vegetable and fruit garden practically for free using materials found in the forest - soil, compost, mulch, carbon, fertilizer and wood.
I cleared 1/4 of an acre of deciduous forest and built hugelkultur mounds and raised beds to grow an abundance of vegetables in the 1st year. In the following 3 years, I started spending money to build up the infrastructure for a productive food forest system that my family can benefit from for generations. Today, we’re harvesting our first fruit from the trees and harvesting an abundance of berries, vegetables and eggs as well as wild game from the surrounding forest.
Log Cabin Building, Bushcraft, Survival Skills, Cooking, Canadian Wilderness, Off Grid Living, Homesteading 
Apple Podcast: https://apple.co/40OgrDO
Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/show/7pym84TIpDlbOagIrjDoWU?si=87a26de90e0e41b5
Podcast: https://www.buzzsprout.com/2261599/episodes
Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/myselfreliance
Rumble: https://rumble.com/c/MySelfReliance

Hi, I'm Shawn James. I am a passionate outdoorsman living the life of my dreams in a log cabin that I built by myself in the Canadian wilderness. localized.title: 4 Year Garden Evolution | How to Start a Garden from Scratch on a Budget
localized.description:
Go to https://drinkag1.com/myselfreliance to get a FREE 1-year supply of Vitamin D3+K2 and 5 AG1 travel packs with your first purchase. Thanks
 to AG1 for sponsoring today's video!
At the beginning of 2020, I started a vegetable and fruit garden practically for free using materials found in the forest - soil, compost, mulch, carbon, fertilizer and wood.
I cleared 1/4 of an acre of deciduous forest and built hugelkultur mounds and raised beds to grow an abundance of vegetables in the 1st year. In the following 3 years, I started spending money to build up the infrastructure for a productive food forest system that my family can benefit from for generations. Today, we’re harvesting our first fruit from the trees and harvesting an abundance of berries, vegetables and eggs as well as wild game from the surrounding forest.
Log Cabin Building, Bushcraft, Survival Skills, Cooking, Canadian Wilderness, Off Grid Living, Homesteading

snippet.title: Taking Our Forest Cabin To The Next Level!
snippet.description:
In this weeks episode, we take our cabin build to the next level adding outdoor extensions and fitting out the interior!  Discover June’s Journey for FREE! Tap here to download: https://woo.ga/sj4axj1d Play on Android, iOS, and PC through Facebook Games.

Here, we take our cool Palmako kit-set cabin that we constructed in last weeks episode (view here: https://youtu.be/LzmHQuFsG_Q) and take the cabin build to the next level, creating decks and awnings which really help to connect the cabin to the outdoors and doing a full cabinetry fit-out on the interior.

The front deck will be such a nice place to sit and enjoy all day sun, as well as a great place to BBQ and entertain. The interior fit-out will provide a huge amount of function and storage as we add a kitchenette, shelving, build-in-wardrobes and more. I think my absolute favourite addition though has to be the rear tree-house style deck, with stunning views looking out into the forest. 

To find out more about these cabins, visit: https://www.palmako.ee/en-us/houses?utm_medium=referral&utm_source=LivingBigInATinyHouse&utm_campaign=Living+Big+Video+Campaign&utm_content=Living+Big+Video+Campaign

You can find Palmako kit-set cabins all over the globe! Find your local distributor here: https://www.palmako.ee/en/find-your-nearest-reseller?utm_medium=referral&utm_source=LivingBigInATinyHouse&utm_campaign=Living+Big+Video+Campaign&utm_content=Living+Big+Video+Campaign

We hope you enjoy this episode! 

If you enjoy our show and would like to help support our work, please consider supporting us on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/livingbig

Our Socials and Links: https://linktr.ee/livingbig

Find out more about this tiny house and others on our website: https://www.livingbiginatinyhouse.com/

Please subscribe for more videos on tiny houses, architecture, DIY, design, and sustainable, off-grid living.

🏡 Meet Tiffany, a multi-talented 22-year-old who built her own tiny house with the help of her dad & other family members. It features a creative staircase vanity and pull-out closet system that stores 40 shoes! The idea to build a tiny house on wheels began as a high school project. After graduating, she built her 150 sqft tiny house for cash over 3 years. It cost her less than $18k, thanks to her resourcefulness & Fb Marketplace scores. During the process, she fell in love and added a gaming setup in the loft for her husband. Now, their tiny home is parked on their own land, where they're renovating the main house to rent, creating lush outdoor living space, and building a shed conversion man-cave.

snippet.title: She Custom Designed Her Gorgeous Tiny House w/ MASSIVE kitchen
snippet.description:
Her Links:
FREE GIFT! Juicy Love Bedroom Empowerment - http://eepurl.com/iL4tzA
Vixen Academy:  https://thevixenacademy.com/
LG Quiz: http://eepurl.com/hp6EkL
YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/@staceyvixenacademy/videos
Media/Press: https://thevixenacademy.com/staceymurphymedia/

Please note: mysticdesignbystacey@gmail.com has been changed to vixenacademy@gmail.com

Interested In Being Featured On The Channel? : http://bit.ly/Tour-Application

VIDEO DESCRIPTION:

Join Stacey as she takes viewers on a tour of her beautiful tiny home, the Tiny Vixen. Designed with women in mind, this home is vibrant, functional, and cozy, showcasing how tiny living can be both spacious and welcoming. If you're a woman considering tiny living, this tour is for you!

Vibrant Living Room for Connection and Community
When stepping into Stacey's living room, the first thing you'll notice is the vibrant art that brings the space to life. She designed this room to be a TV-free zone focused on connection and community. The seating area is perfect for putting on shoes or leaning against the credenza. This space is all about creating a welcoming atmosphere for friends and family.

Heart of the Home: The Kitchen
The kitchen is the heart of Stacey's tiny home, and it was essential to her to have a functional and beautiful space. She worked with her builder to create more counter space by relocating the refrigerator and adding open shelves. The kitchen features a gas cooktop, a deep sink, and a Panasonic 4-in-1 appliance that bakes, air fries, sautés, and pressure cooks. The kitchen is designed for both cooking and socializing, making it perfect for hosting.

Cozy and Functional Bathroom
Though it's the smallest room in the house, Stacey's bathroom packs a mighty punch. It features wallpaper for a pop of color and a rain shower for a luxurious feel. She also included a crystal and plants to enhance the energy of the space. The quartz countertop and gold accents make the bathroom feel like a spa.

Practical Laundry and Storage Solutions
In the hallway, Stacey opted for a washer and dryer instead of a linen closet, making it a practical choice for tiny living. The broom closet and pantry provide additional storage space. This setup ensures that every inch of space is used efficiently.

Meditation and Zen Space
Stacey's loft serves as a meditation room and office, divided by a bookshelf with plants. The serene environment is perfect for starting the day with meditation and capturing inspiration for her coaching and business. The space also includes a TV area with a pop of blue for relaxation.

Mystic Design Bedroom
The bedroom is Stacey's sanctuary with a Mystic design, featuring artwork that brings the space to life. The dresser bay and three shades of pink make the room feel larger and more inviting. The closet offers ample storage, and the step stool helps her reach everything. The double bed provides walking space and complements the aesthetic of the room.

Empowerment and Connection
Stacey believes in using her home as a 3D vision board to manifest love, health, and wealth. The Mystic design elements throughout the Tiny Vixen reflect this philosophy. She encourages viewers to explore their own Mystic design with the free Bedroom Empowerment gift linked in the description.

Join the Tiny Living Movement
Tiny living is becoming an essential solution to housing affordability. Stacey's journey from New York to Orlando and finally to California has shown her the transformative power of tiny living. She's passionate about advocating for this lifestyle and helping others find security and joy in tiny spaces.

Connect with Stacy
If you have questions about tiny living, design tips, or her cross-country journey, feel free to reach out to her at mysticddesignbystacey@gmail.com or visit her website at mysticddesignbystacey.com. Thank you for joining her on this tour of the Tiny Vixen!

Tags:
#tinyliving  #tinyhometours  #rvlife  #tinyhousedesign #empowerment  #minimalistliving  #livingtiny  #nomadlife  #mobileliving

snippet.title: Fresh Rosemary and Mint Soap
snippet.description:
Fresh Rosemary and Mint Soap - Cold Process

In this video, mom experimented on using fresh rosemary leaves and mint leaves from the garden to give color and fragrance. The color turned out dark green. The smell is nice and maybe because of the peppermint essential oil.

This basic soap recipe is from "Homestead Blessings"
https://youtu.be/PkG4CilngNw?si=9vApLeAzH61KVQ-4

Here are the basic ingredients:
4 cups water
48 oz vegetable shortening (Crisco)
32 oz coconut oil
16 oz olive oil
12 oz lye (use food-grade)

#rosemary 
#soap 
#mint 
#homemade 
#coldprocesssoap

snippet.title: Beginner's Guide to Cold Process Soap | Bramble Berry Basics of Soap Making
snippet.description:
If you want to customize soap down to the last ingredient, cold process is a great option. Cold process soap is made by combining oils and sodium hydroxide lye. That causes a chemical reaction called saponification. Melt and pour soap has already gone through that process. 

Once you find your perfect recipe you can start getting creative with the designs. You get to choose the oils, colorants, scents, and more. In this video, we go over the basic tools and ingredients you need to get started. We also go over safety when working with lye, how to make soap, and how to clean up. Find more resources below!

Articles About Soap Making:
• Guide to Cold Process Soap: https://bberry.studio/BeginnersColdProcessGuide
• Guide to Lye Safety: https://bberry.studio/BeginnerLyeSafety
• How to Formulate Cold Process: https://bberry.studio/BeginnerFormulatingCP
• Tools for Cold Process Soap Making: https://bberry.studio/ToolsForColdProcess

Find more articles and recipes here: https://bberry.studio/IntheStudio_Projects

Find more videos on the Basics of Soap Making here: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLr_YF9AaZRqj8bJwX3wwie3-p6bRpkbQC

Timestamps:
00:00 - Introduction
01:59 - Why Make Cold Process Soap
03:21 - Cold Process Ingredients
05:42 - Tools for Cold Process
09:09 - Prep to Make Soap
14:27 - How to Make Cold Process Soap
20:02 - Cleaning Up Cold Process Soap
21:32 - Answering Your Questions!

Any equipment used for soap making should be exclusive – don’t use it for food. Lye and fragrance can get stuck in cracks, even with thorough washing. We also recommend hand washing instead of using the dishwasher.

Tools for Cold Process Soap Making: https://bberry.studio/ToolsForColdProcess

snippet.title: How to Formulate Cold Process Soap Recipes | Bramble Berry Basics of Soap Making
snippet.description:
Formulating your own cold process soap recipes is easy! In this video, Bramble Berry CEO and Founder, Anne-Marie Faiola, goes over the basics of formulating cold process soap recipes. 

To create your own recipe, start by choosing your base oils. You can use each one around 20-30%. For the remaining portion, consider what you’d like the bar to feel like. Do you want it to be super moisturizing, have a nice thick lather, or to be hard and long lasting? How you want your soap to feel and look will guide you in choosing your oils.

You can never go wrong with a 34/33/33 ratio. That’s 34% olive oil, 33% coconut oil, and 33% palm oil. They’re commonly used because they complement each other well. Palm oil acts as a secondary lathering agent and hardens the soap, coconut oil is cleansing and produces big bubbles, and olive oil is moisturizing and gives bars a silky feeling. 

Looking for more information on how to formulate cold process soap recipes? These articles can help!

 • Formulating Cold Process Soap Recipes:
 https://bberry.studio/FormulatingCP

 • Beginner's Guide to Common Soapmaking Oils: 
https://bberry.studio/BeginnersGuidetoOils

• How to Substitute Oils in Cold Process Soap Recipes:
https://bberry.studio/HowtoSubOIls

• Palm Oil Alternatives in Cold Process Soap Recipes:
https://www.brambleberry.com/ingredient-information/oils-and-butters/art0028-palm-oil-alternatives-in-cold-process-soap.html

snippet.title: How to Make Simple and Gentle Soap - Perfect for Beginners! | Bramble Berry
snippet.description:
This cold process recipe is designed for beginners. It has simple ingredients that are easy to work with. It's the perfect recipe to try cold process soap for the first time! 

💮 Simple and Gentle Soap Project: https://bberry.studio/SimpleGentleSoap

This recipe is made with coconut oil, palm oil, and olive oil. They’re commonly used because they complement each other well. Palm oil acts as a secondary lathering agent and hardens the soap, coconut oil is cleansing and produces big bubbles, and olive oil is moisturizing and gives the bars a silky feeling. 

💮 Coconut Oil: https://bberry.studio/CoconutOil

The soap is unscented and uncolored to keep things easy. Once you have a few batches under your belt, you can start experimenting with additives. For the mold, you can use almost any box or container that you have on hand. You'll just need to line it with freezer paper so the soap doesn't stick.

💮 Simple and Gentle Soap recipe:
8 oz. Coconut Oil (24%)
15 oz. Olive Oil (44%)
11 oz. Palm Oil (32%)
4.8 oz. Lye
11.2 oz. Distilled Water

💮 Key Terms:
• Saponification: The chemical reaction that occurs when oil and lye molecules create new soap molecules.
• Trace: The point when oils and lye water emulsify and begin to thicken. Once the soap has reached thin trace, it will continue to thicken as it sits. 
• Emulsify: When the oils and lye solution mix and don't separate. The term emulsify and trace are often used interchangeably.
• Superfat: Any extra oil that's not turned into soap. 
• Gel phase: "Gelling" or "gel phase" refers to when the soap gets warm and gelatinous – up to 180° F. Gel phase results in brighter colors and a shinier, more translucent appearance. 
• Soda ash: When unsaponified lye reacts with naturally-occurring carbon dioxide in the air and creates a white ashy film on the bars. It only affects the way the soap looks, not the quality.

snippet.title: Pine Tar Soap for Men - Cold Process - recipe included
snippet.description:
Pine Tar Soap for Men

I watched a lot of YouTube videos before trying my hand at this recipe. I learned a lot of Do’s and Don’s along the way.  I was nervous that it would accelerate after adding the Pine Tar to the soap mixture, but luckily it did not; and I ended up creating a nice manly-scented loaf of Pine Tar soap.

The fragrances used are listed below and created much more than I used in this recipe.

* 100g Palo Santo from Midwest Fragrance Company - https://midwestfragranceco.com/products/palo-santo-fragrance-oil?_pos=1&_sid=fad067f8e&_ss=r
* 100g Smoked Cedar & Old from Midwest Fragrance Company - https://midwestfragranceco.com/products/smoked-cedar-oud-fragrance-oil?_pos=1&_sid=f89fc8bec&_ss=r
* 21g Pine Needle Essential Oil from Amazon - https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07895B2VZ/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1
* 60g Bourbon Tobacco from Wholesale Supplies Plus - https://www.wholesalesuppliesplus.com/products/bourboned-tobacco-fragrance-oil.aspx
* 21g Black Pepper from Wholesale Supplies Plus - https://www.wholesalesuppliesplus.com/products/black-pepper-fragrance-oil.aspx



Other Items used in this recipe:

* White Kaolin Clay: https://www.wholesalesuppliesplus.com/products/white-kaolin-clay.aspx
* 80oz. Soap mold: https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0BGQ9GGH8/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&th=1
* The Multi-Cutter Soap Cutter is from Etsy - the shop it no longer listed, but there are many others on Etsy.

https://uppbeat.io/t/hartzmann/life-mood
* Music from #Uppbeat (free for Creators!):
https://uppbeat.io/t/jonny-boyle/tres-french

snippet.title: Crystal Clear Transparent Soap -  Part 1 (Detailed Explanation)
snippet.description:
#transparentsoap  #soapncrafts #hotprocesssoap #soapbase #diy 
Check The Ultra Clear Transparent Soap Base Video Tutorials online: http://www.soapNcrafts.com

*** If you have question or comment, please leave in the comment area! In the next video, I'll demonstrate a foaming test and include a FAQ section to address the most frequently asked questions.***

It's Mellen from soapNcrafts. I'm delighted to welcome you back to my channel! I am very lazy to talk, so I used AI to clone my voice and talk in this video!

3 years ago, I uploaded a video titled "Make Crystal Clear Soap in Less than 10 Minutes." https://youtu.be/FXTZTHLahb0  That video garnered over 19 million views and received five thousand likes (Thank you!) However, it also generated numerous questions about the method used. 

As a result, I've decided to revisit the topic and provide a more detailed, step-by-step guide with thorough explanations. Additionally, I'll address some frequently asked questions towards the end of this video. My aim is to ensure that you have a comprehensive understanding of this method. 

The primary goal of creating crystal clear transparent soap is to push the boundaries of transparency to its highest possible level. In this video, our focus is not on teaching you how to make soap base from scratch. Additionally, we won't be addressing concerns such as alcohol smell, sweat, foaming, or soap hardness. If you're interested in learning how to make transparent soap base, you can find a detailed tutorial on my website. Simply click the link in the top right corner. Furthermore, if you purchase the tutorial, assistance is available in our Facebook group. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ingredients for Crystal Clear Soap (Alcohol Method) 

A - Oil (95C/203F)
Fractionated Coconut Oil ........................ 140g (4.9oz)
Stearic Acid ............................................... 60g (2.1oz) 
Glycerin .................................................. 400g (14.1oz)

B - Lye (80C/176F)
NaOH ......................................................... 41g (1.5oz)
H2O ............................................................ 82g (2.9oz)

C - Solvent (ROOM TEMP)
99% Alcohol .......................................... 300g (10.6oz)

***If you are using solid coconut oil, please change the 
NaOH to 34g (1.2oz), Water to 68g (2.4oz)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

It's Mellen from soapNcrafts. I'm delighted to welcome you back to my channel! I am very lazy to talk, so I used AI to clone my voice and talk in this video!

3 years ago, I uploaded a video titled "Make Crystal Clear Soap in Less than 10 Minutes." https://youtu.be/FXTZTHLahb0  That video garnered over 19 million views and received five thousand likes (Thank you!) However, it also generated numerous questions about the method used. 

As a result, I've decided to revisit the topic and provide a more detailed, step-by-step guide with thorough explanations. Additionally, I'll address some frequently asked questions towards the end of this video. My aim is to ensure that you have a comprehensive understanding of this method. 

The primary goal of creating crystal clear transparent soap is to push the boundaries of transparency to its highest possible level. In this video, our focus is not on teaching you how to make soap base from scratch. Additionally, we won't be addressing concerns such as alcohol smell, sweat, foaming, or soap hardness. If you're interested in learning how to make transparent soap base, you can find a detailed tutorial on my website. Simply click the link in the top right corner. Furthermore, if you purchase the tutorial, assistance is available in our Facebook group. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ingredients for Crystal Clear Soap (Alcohol Method) 

A - Oil (95C/203F)
Fractionated Coconut Oil ........................ 140g (4.9oz)
Stearic Acid ............................................... 60g (2.1oz) 
Glycerin .................................................. 400g (14.1oz)

B - Lye (80C/176F)
NaOH ......................................................... 41g (1.5oz)
H2O ............................................................ 82g (2.9oz)

C - Solvent (ROOM TEMP)
99% Alcohol .......................................... 300g (10.6oz)

***If you are using solid coconut oil, please change the 
NaOH to 34g (1.2oz), Water to 68g (2.4oz)

snippet.title: Finally! Step By Step Method For Making Crystal Clear Glycerin Soap At Home The Easy Way!
snippet.description:
#glycerinesoap #soapmaking #handmade #handmadesoap -  For crying out loud! This is DEFINITELY the updated and correct version of this transparent soap recipe and method, after uploading the wrong edit not once, but TWICE! 

Never have to buy pricey Stephensons transparent melt & pour base ever again by making your very own transparent soap base at home.  This is a reboot of an earlier video. How to make transparent soap appears to be a popular search, so it seems weird that my earlier video was low on views (YT algorithms?). So, I thought I'd reboot it and give it another go in the hope it reaches more people who, like me, have struggled to find a user-friendly transparent soap recipe to make at home. When I was exploring making my own transparent soap from scratch, most of the videos I could find seemed a bit too scientific, overly complicated, involved a microwave and less accessible ingredients, moreover, they were mostly from countries which weren't English speaking and therefore the only details were from sketchy auto translations! A bit more research led me to a couple of transparent soap recipes, using hot process soap making methods in a crockpot, and to me, these seemed far easier for homemade soap making. However, all the crockpot recipes stemmed from the United States, were in imperial measures and used American brand name products, like Everclear, that we don't have in the UK. Soooo, I endeavoured to formulate my own transparent soap recipe, in grams, using more generic ingredients that, hopefully, can be found and purchased the world over.

3. Takes the required quantity of coconut oil and mix with the lay solution.
4. heat up the mixture.
5. After getting thick solution, pour into container

snippet.title: 🌴 100% coconut oil soap for bathing -  3 ingredients - no stick blender soap
snippet.description:
This is a simple recipe for 100% coconut oil soap that can be used for bathing. Coconut oil soap is well known for its great lather and strong cleaning power, but it can be drying to the skin, so this recipe uses a high 25% superfat to make the soap more gentle and suitable for bathing and hand washing. 

All the recipe details are below, including a half size and low superfat version of the recipe for cleaning. 

*Recipe details*
The Video Recipe - 25% superfat - large batch
840g coconut oil
234g water (any drinking water is fine)
This recipe uses a 2:1 water to lye ratio (33% lye concentration) for the water-lye solution. 
115g sodium hydroxide / NaOH

This recipe makes just under 1200g of soap (12 x 100g bars)
You will need a mould that holds at least 1.2 litres or 40.5 fluid ounces of liquid to make this recipe.

Half Sized Recipe - 25% superfat
420g coconut oil
117g water
57g sodium hydroxide / NaOH

Lower superfat recipe for cleaning soap (will be drying on skin)
840g coconut oil
292g water
146g sodium hydroxide (5% superfat)

METHOD as per video
If you make the low superfat version for a cleaning soap, be prepared for it to saponify faster and go through a more vigorous and hotter 'gel phase', particularly if made in a loaf mould. Do not insulate this soap after it's poured, just leave it uncovered (it will get hot!).  

*New to soap making? This is important!*
Sodium hydroxide and potassium hydroxide (lyes) used in soap making, in granular or flake form or in solution with water/other liquids, as well as raw soap batter, are highly corrosive and require careful and attentive handling and the proper use of personal protective equipment. Please watch this video to learn more about essential soap making safety precautions https://youtu.be/EZTsW9UvNmU

snippet.title: Soap Making Tutorial for Beginners - Full Demonstration & Cold Process Soap Beginner Recipe
snippet.description:
Welcome to my soap making tutorial for beginners. This video demonstrates the full method for cold process soap making using an easy beginner recipe (scroll down for details). 

*This soap after two years in storage* https://youtu.be/YUJbKwNgwmA
*My updated cold process lavender soap recipe* https://youtu.be/s37ZY6yDWdE
*Blog link* https://www.ellyseveryday.com/ellys-everyday-blog/new-cold-process-lavender-soap-recipe
 
*IMPORTANT UPDATES*
🎈 Please store your lye solution in a polypropylene plastic container instead of glass! Or don't store it at all and make it fresh :) 

Also, please be aware that this recipe is almost a castile soap! It's not really an all-rounder recipe, just what I came up with at the time (I honestly had no idea it would be so popular! It was my first soap recipe shared on youtube and I thought only a few of my friends would see it 😬). Please check out my other videos for more balanced recipes. I have so many wonderful soap recipes on this channel! 🌸

*New to soap making? This is important!*
Sodium hydroxide and potassium hydroxide (lyes) used in soap making, in granular or flake form or in solution with water/other liquids, as well as raw soap batter, are highly corrosive and require careful and attentive handling and the proper use of personal protective equipment. Please watch this video to learn more about essential soap making safety precautions https://youtu.be/EZTsW9UvNmU
Web page https://www.ellyseveryday.com/introduction-to-soap-making

*Recipe details* 
My mould used in this video is 37cm long, 7cm wide and 5.7cm deep
It holds 1.480kg of soap batter - just enough for this recipe.

Ingredients:
    •  950 grams olive oil  
    •  50 grams coconut oil 
    •  199 grams water 
    •  133 grams caustic soda (also known as sodium hydroxide)
    •  20-50 grams of essential oil (optional - I used 40g lavender EO *please check your supplier for usage rates)
    •  Lavender buds, clay or colours for your soap (optional) 

*To buy me a coffee:* 
https://www.buymeacoffee.com/ellyseveryday

snippet.title: Using palm oil in soap making. Should we, or not? What do we need to know? (it's complicated)
snippet.description:
This video discusses everything I've learned about palm oil and soap making. What is palm oil? What is it used for? Why is it in everything!? What are the issues and problems with it (eg. deforestation/habitat loss)? Why is palm oil so good for soap making? Do we need to avoid it in our soap recipes? What to do!!??? 🤯

*Thank you to this video's sponsor:*
New Directions Australia https://www.newdirections.com.au/ 
5kg bucket Certified Organic Palm Oil as shown in the video:
https://www.newdirections.com.au/epages/newdirections.sf/en_AU/?ObjectPath=/Shops/newdirections/Products/OCOV5KPALM

*References and further reading:* 
IUCN issues brief on palm oil and biodiversity
https://www.iucn.org/resources/issues-brief/palm-oil-and-biodiversity
WWF web page about Palm Oil https://wwf.org.au/what-we-do/food/palm-oil/
Roundtable on Sustainable Palm Oil https://rspo.org/
My video: Choosing oils for soap making https://youtu.be/V-uDPifp3n0
The Guardian: 'How the World Got Hooked on Palm Oil' 
https://www.theguardian.com/news/2019/feb/19/palm-oil-ingredient-biscuits-shampoo-environmental
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palm_oil
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elaeis_guineensis

snippet.title: 🧼🫧Soap Challenge Club cold process soap making spin swirl variation.🫧🧼
snippet.description:
This was my entry for the June 2024 Soap Challenge, where we had to make a spin swirl cold process soap. We were allowed to use any mould and pour our soap into the mould however we liked, once poured we then had to spin the soap to create curls or curves in the soap.

snippet.title: I GOT LUCKY HOME DECOR THRIFTING IN GOODWILL TODAY! THRIFT WITH ME
snippet.description:
Let’s go Home decor THRIFTING IN GOODWILL TODAY! Come THRIFT WITH ME  + I’ll share A HUGE THRIFT SHOPPING HAUL styled!

Today on Thrilled Thrifter we are THRIFT SHOPPING IN GOODWILL & I have a THRIFT HAUL. So come THRIFT WITH ME  and see WHAT I BUY. 

My thrifting channel:​⁠ @ThrilledThrifter 
​⁠ Thrilled Thrifter family channel : ​⁠ @thrilledthrifterhome 

Email me at:thrilledthrifter@gmail.com
Instagram ~ julie_thrilledthrifter

Hello everyone, my name is Julie and on Thrilled Thrifter you will find that I absolutely love thrift shopping.(Especially for home decor!) I share all things thrift here on my channel to teach you how to go thrifting for your home, family and friends. {I'm not a reseller!}  I mostly thrift at Goodwill, yard/garage sales, FB marketplace, antique stores, estate sales and so many other local thrift stores. I believe you can make your home beautiful on a thrifty budget! I will take you on so many thrift with me shopping trips, share my thrift hauls and almost always show you how to use thrift finds in your home. I post every Friday and sometimes on Tuesday. Occasionally I do thrift flips and decorating videos too! I hope you walk away from my channel  feeling inspired to shop secondhand. Don't forget to subscribe so you don't miss out!


Thrift With Me playlist : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNRTCy9w_mAxc9ZkkrbqhwuL

snippet.title: THRIFTING GOODWILL  FOR MY HOME & THRIFT HAUL * THRIFT WITH ME FOR HOME DECOR & MORE
snippet.description:
Today I have a RELAXING THRIFT WITH ME on YOUTUBE video! Let’s THRIFTING for THRIFTED HOME DECOR and after THRIFT SHOPPING i will share my THRIFT HAUL with you.
My YouTube thrifting channel:​⁠ ​⁠​⁠​⁠ @ThrilledThrifter ​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠ ​⁠​⁠ ​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠​​⁠ 
Thrilled Thrifter Home & family channel : ​⁠ @thrilledthrifterhome ​⁠ ​⁠​⁠ ​⁠​⁠ ​⁠​​⁠ ​​⁠​​⁠​⁠​⁠ 

Email me at:thrilledthrifter@gmail.com
Instagram ~ julie_thrilledthrifter

Hello everyone, my name is Julie and on Thrilled Thrifter you will find that I absolutely love thrift shopping.(Especially for home decor!) I share all things thrift here on my channel to teach you how to go thrifting for your home, family and friends. {I'm not a reseller!}  I mostly thrift at Goodwill, yard/garage sales, FB marketplace, antique stores, estate sales and so many other local thrift stores. I believe you can make your home beautiful on a thrifty budget! I will take you on so many thrift with me shopping trips, share my thrift hauls and almost always show you how to use thrift finds in your home. I post every Friday and sometimes on Tuesday. Occasionally I do thrift flips and decorating videos too! I hope you walk away from my channel  feeling inspired to shop secondhand. Don't forget to subscribe so you don't miss out!


Thrift With Me playlist : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNRTCy9w_mAxc9ZkkrbqhwuL

Thrift haul only playlist : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNRC18loYPeJ-UKw2_VjMVBs

Thrifting and DIY makeover playlist : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNSiF_9quag9lCnPKp9_xOUH

Thriftmas 2023: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNTwN8vIATPQmKdru19CFvVK&si=JPK-gIaoGiU4FuwJ

VLOGMAS / THRIFT- MAS PLAYLIST : https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLHAcKl7RGbNSIDFbvkWwlUsfw7lpSPVVQ

* Some links are affiliate links. This is no extra charge to you but it could help the Thrilled Thrifter family so much if you choose the links I provide. Thank you so much for supporting my family.

snippet.title: A Review of: Creating Home: Design for Living by Keith Summerour & Pressing Hydrangea Blossoms
snippet.description:
20% off Code in Ollny Store: NEW20
Offer Expires: July 20th, 2024
Ollny 740 Cluster Lights: https://shorturl.at/pDogf

"From acclaimed architect and designer Keith Summerour comes an alluring new book of carefully crafted dwellings that redefine the idea of home for today.
 
When we think about what home is, many of us would say a house that is soulful and welcoming, a place with an inviting porch and a lush garden, a welcoming entryway and well-crafted living spaces that will nurture our private moments and expand to welcome guests. In this alluring new book, Keith Summerour shares nine houses, exploring their architecture, interiors, and grounds, to illustrate a new idea of home. Reinterpreting and making new his own Southern legacy that speaks both of aristocratic charm and homespun appeal, these homes range from rustic retreats that draw their power from the land to elegant manor houses, but all share extraordinary character and charm that nod to history while reflecting the way people wish to live in the world today.
 
Enriched by the work of some of the top interior decorators working today, including Beth Webb, Barbara Westbrook, Circa Interiors, and Liza Bryan, as well as world-renowned landscape designers Jeremy Smearman and John Howard, and beautifully illustrated with all-new photography, Creating Home is the ultimate dream book."

Thumbnail Photo Interior Design by JARED HUGHES and photo by Hector Sanchez

snippet.title: 5 Homes You Can Buy On Amazon For Under 30K
snippet.description:
Amazon actually has REAL homes for under 30K, not just house plans, but real tiny homes suitable for living. Amazon, known for its vast inventory, offers a variety of houses. Many of these homes can be equipped with insulation and electricity, making them viable for year-round living. The cost-effectiveness of buying versus building a tiny house depends on your DIY skills; while assembling these kits requires some handy work, constructing one from scratch is considerably more complex and potentially more costly, especially if you plan to insulate it for all-season use. If you're ready to embrace a compact lifestyle, Amazon has made it surprisingly easy to get started.

snippet.title: SHOCKING Hidden Costs Of Manufactured (Mobile) Homes
snippet.description:

snippet.title: INSURANCE Will DESTROY EVER Getting An Affordable Home
snippet.description:
As insurance companies nationwide raise their rates for flood and fire coverage, the dream of owning an affordable home is becoming increasingly elusive. These skyrocketing premiums are driven by the rising frequency and severity of natural disasters, making it more expensive for homeowners to protect their properties. Consequently, the overall cost of homeownership is climbing, putting additional financial strain on prospective buyers. This surge in insurance costs is particularly burdensome for those already struggling to find affordable housing, as it adds yet another barrier to entry in an already challenging market. With insurance becoming a significant expense, the goal of securing a reasonably priced home is further out of reach for many Americans.

 #prefabhomes #BookingComHosts #Ad  Unlock amazing booking opportunities today by registering your short-term rental property on Booking.com.  https://alwr.io/rljHXw 

Construction prices for homes or unique rentals can be very expensive these days.  Here are the Top 5 unique home build options that can be built for less than $100k: 1. Garden Shed 2. Aframe Kit 3. Container Home 4. Geodome 5. Custom Tiny Home. I've built all but one of these and they're DIY friendly as well as easy on the wallet if you don't go crazy with finishes.   And before anyone complains about price per sq.ft., smaller homes will ALWAYS have a higher cost because you have basic sunk investments that are required no matter what size home - i.e. utilities, kitchen, bathroom(s), roofing, etc.  The first 700 sq.ft. of the home is always more expensive.  It gets drastically cheaper the larger you go (within reason).
